Class Link

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.nau.elc.hardlinks.domain.Link

  • public class Link
extends java.lang.Object

      • levDist

        private static int levDist(java.lang.String s0,
                           java.lang.String s1)
        Gets the Levenshtein Distance between two strings. Copied from WikiBooks.

        This is used to find likely candidates for a filename match in the exported Content Collection. Because non-ASCII characters are handled differently in the XML than they are in the ZIP file entities, we just want to find the closest match, rather than an exact one.
        Parameters:
        s0 - The first string.
        s1 - The second string.
        Returns:
        The "edit distance" between the two (see WikiBooks link for more information).

      • isAllASCII

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        whether or not there are non-ASCII characters.
